title: Skilled Independent visa (subclass 189)
content_text: The Skilled Independent visa (subclass 189) is a permanent residence visa for invited workers and New Zealand citizens with skills Australia needs. With this visa you can: stay in Australia indefinitely, work and study in Australia, enrol in Medicare, sponsor relatives for permanent residence, travel to and from Australia for 5 years, and if eligible, become an Australian citizen. You must be invited to apply for this visa. To be invited you need to submit an Expression of Interest through SkillSelect...

title: Express Entry: How it works
content_text: Express Entry is an application management system for skilled workers who want to immigrate to Canada permanently and live and work there. There are 3 immigration programs managed through Express Entry: Federal Skilled Worker Program, Federal Skilled Trades Program, and Canadian Experience Class. To apply, you need to create an online profile. If you meet the criteria, you'll be placed in a pool of candidates. We'll invite the highest-ranking candidates to apply for permanent residence...
